properties.headline: BUSH FIRE - KOSCIUSZKO NATIONAL PARK all access roads to the park
properties.otherAdvice:
The Kosciuszko National Park will remain closed until further notice due to the impact of recent fires and active fires still being managed.

For closed parks this means no public access at all, including tracks, trails, campgrounds and picnic areas. This is an important safety measure to protect the public.

Therefore all access roads into the park are closed to the public.

Access to Perisher, Smiggins, Guthega & Charlotte Pass is strictly limited to essential staff by authorisation from the resort operators and current lessees/lodge managers residing on their premises by authorisation issued by National Parks and Wildlife Service. For access email npws.southernrangesbranch@environment.nsw.gov.au between the hours of 8:30am and 4:30pm.
